      "message": "lint script hardcodes a single test file — future .ts tests will silently escape linting\n\n```\n\"lint\": \"eslint src scripts golar.config.ts openapi-ts.config.ts tests/unit/redfish-spec-patch.spec.ts\"\n```\n\n\nThe lint target is pinned to one specific file, tests/unit/redfish-spec-patch.spec.ts. Any future .ts test added under tests/unit/ won\u0027t be linted, so it can pass npm run lint while violating the rules and CI won\u0027t catch it.\n\nThis also contradicts the ESLint config: eslint.config.js already has a vitest-config block scoped to **/tests/unit/**/*.spec.{j,t}s?(x), so the rules are written for all test files — only the script narrows coverage to one.\n\nSuggest linting directories instead of individual files:\n\n\n```suggestion\n       \"lint\": \"eslint src scripts tests openapi-ts.config.ts golar.config.ts\",\n```",
